Certainly! You can use MATLAB to perform this operation easily. Here's a simple script to subtract 9 from each element of the given vector and store the result in a new vector:

```matlab
% Original vector
original_vector = [5, 3, 7, 2, 4];

% Subtract 9 from each element
new_vector = original_vector - 9;

% Display the new vector
disp(new_vector);
```

When you run this code in MATLAB, it will display the new vector as the output, which is the result of subtracting 9 from each element of the original vector.
